#13)Nucleotide Composition. Write a script that:

#determines the unique characters in this sequence
#iterate over each unique character and count the number found in the sequence store each count in a dictionary. example: nt_comp['A']=2
#when you are done counting each character calculate and report the nucleotide composition and the GC content.

sequencia=list('')

dna=set(sequencia)

nucDict={}    #criação de um dicionário com valorem em aberto. 

for caracteres in sorted(dna):
  count = sequencia.count(caracteres)
  nucDict[caracteres]=count
  print(caracteres, count)

GC = (nucDict['G'] + nucDict['C'])/len(sequencia) #é preciso separar a contagem das bases GC do restante do código, se não da errado. 
print("GC content = {:.2}".format(GC))  #irá somar os 537 de C com 430 de G e dividir pela total. 